t teaching converge in this book, which attempts to shed light on a question that is often asked in either ESL or EFL teaching contexts: is teaching about gender-related topics (including controversial sociopolitical topics) in the language classroom education or indoctrination?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Study & Teaching.2bisacsh  aELT.  aFeminist pedagogy.  aFeminist qualitative research.  aGender and language.  aJapan.  aTeacher cognition.  aTeacher identity.  afeminism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066312908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMultiLingual Matters eBook Package 2015-2017z978311060670640uhttps://doi.org/10.21832/978178309802640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781783098026423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781783098026/original  a978-3-11-060670-6  MultiLingual Matters eBook Package 2015-2017c2015d2017  a978-3-11-066312-9  MultiLingual Matters Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK